subject: Athletics and Sports
lead_paragraph: Tommy Tuberville, coach of No. 18 Auburn, would not discuss reports that his name was high on the list of candidates if Texas A&M were to fire Coach Dennis Franchione. “As I told our players, that’s the least of our worries or anybody’s worries,” Tuberville, a former Texas A&M defensive coordinator, said.Meanwhile, Franchione denied reports that he was negotiating a contract buyout. Texas A&M said Monday that Athletic Director Bill Byrne would wait until the season ended before evaluating Franchione.
